==English==
'''thy'''

===Etymology===
:From the Middle English ''thi''.

===[[Pronominal adjective]]===
#That belongs to [[thee]; the possessive form of ''[[thou]]''.
#(''[[Archaic]]'' or ''[[literary]]''): [[your]] (''informal''); that belongs to you (''singular'').

